==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: paraformaldehyde
<hw>par`a*form*al"de*hyde</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>para-</ets> + <ets>formaldehyde</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A polymer of formaldehyde obtained as a white crystalline substance
by concentration of a formaldehyde solution. Formula
<chform>(CH20)n</chform>. It dissolves in hot water with the release of
formaldehyde, and is used as a disinfectant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

